cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.DS

The paper deals with machine learning techniques, specifically Independent Component Analysis (ICA), and proposes an algorithm for efficient hardware implementation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses hardware design, which makes cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions stochastic gradient descent optimization, which is a common optimization technique in machine learning and falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
